# Text-to-Speech Robot ðŸ¤–

A Streamlit-based application that converts text to speech with customizable voice settings.

![App Screenshot](https://img.icons8.com/fluency/200/000000/robot.png)

## Features

- Convert typed text or uploaded text files to speech
- Multiple voice options (Male, Female, Child-like, Older Male)
- Adjustable speech rate and volume
- Download generated audio as MP3
- User-friendly interface with robot theme

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Quratulain-bilal/text-to_speech.git
   cd text-to-speech-robot
Install the required dependencies:

bash
Copy
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the application:

bash
Copy
streamlit run app.py
Usage
Enter text directly or upload a .txt file

Select your preferred voice from the dropdown

Adjust speech rate and volume using the sliders

Click "Convert to Speech" to generate the audio

Play the audio directly or download it as an MP3 file

Requirements
Python 3.7+

Streamlit

pyttsx3

Operating system with TTS engine (Windows works best)

Notes
On Linux systems, you may need to install espeak and ffmpeg:

bash
Copy
sudo apt-get install espeak ffmpeg
Voice options depend on your system's installed TTS voices

